    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix empty output in _activate_dedicated_eps_bearer_context_accept function\n\n### Summary\nThe `_activate_dedicated_eps_bearer_context_accept()` function in the NAS message processing simulator was returning an empty string instead of displaying the relevant EPS bearer context information. This caused unexpected behavior when the function was called during NAS message simulation.\n\nThis fix updates the function to properly display the EPS Bearer Identity (EBI), Procedure Transaction Identity (PTI), and indicates when Protocol Configuration Options (PCO) are present. For consistency, the corresponding `_activate_default_eps_bearer_context_accept()` function was also updated with the same improvements.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/TEST/AS_SIMULATOR/nas_process.c`: Updated both `_activate_dedicated_eps_bearer_context_accept()` and `_activate_default_eps_bearer_context_accept()` functions to display EBI, PTI, and PCO presence information.\n"
}